cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with conversational agents and dialogue history. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper investigates the impact of varying amounts of dialogue history on system performance. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses experimental results to study the effects of dialogue history on training dialogue reward predictors. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with human-human dialogues and their rewards. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses the importance of dialogue history in the overall performance of a conversational system.
